&lt;p&gt;Scrunch and Ahrefs Brand Radar both track brand visibility in AI answers, but they solve different problems. Scrunch is purpose-built for AEO: it monitors AI citations, audits AI crawlability, and actively optimizes how AI bots experience your site. Ahrefs Brand Radar is an add-on to the broader Ahrefs SEO platform, built for teams that want AI visibility alongside traditional search data, backlinks, and web mentions in one place.&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=d4233c10-60b6-46d7-9852-c71dde8507b6&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Free AEO Grader: See Your Brand's Visibility in Answer Engines [Free Tool]" height="58" width="679" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/d4233c10-60b6-46d7-9852-c71dde8507b6.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;If you haven’t benchmarked your AI visibility yet, start with HubSpot’s free &lt;a href="https://www.hubspot.com/aeo-grader"&gt;AEO Grader&lt;/a&gt; — a scored snapshot of how ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini represent your brand today, no account required.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-overview-what-each-actually-tracks"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Overview: What Each Actually Tracks&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-data-methodology-explained"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Data Methodology Explained&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-best-for-teams-and-use-cases"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Best For: Teams and Use Cases&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-pricing-coverage-and-retention"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Pricing, Coverage, and Retention&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-vs-hubspot-aeo-feature-comparison"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs vs HubSpot AEO: Feature Comparison&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-implementation-and-integration"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Implementation and Integration&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-limits-and-what-to-expect"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Limits and What To Expect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#scrunch-vs-ahrefs-how-to-choose"&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs: How To Choose&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#from-visibility-to-action-content-and-pipeline"&gt;From Visibility to Action: Content and Pipeline&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#ahrefs-vs-semrush-in-context"&gt;Ahrefs vs Semrush in Context&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#frequently-asked-questions-about-scrunch-vs-ahrefs"&gt;Frequently Asked Questions About Scrunch vs Ahrefs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Overview: What Each Actually Tracks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Scrunch and Ahrefs Brand Radar are not the same type of product. Understanding what each one actually tracks is the most important step before evaluating pricing, coverage, or ROI.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Scrunch Tracks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Scrunch is a purpose-built AI visibility platform. It tracks brand share of voice across AI answers, sentiment in AI-generated responses, and which domains and pages are most frequently cited. Beyond brand monitoring, it tracks AI search trends for prompt volumes and product-level shopping visibility to show how brands rank in AI-driven purchase recommendations.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Key capabilities include:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Share of voice and sentiment tracking across AI answers&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Citation analysis showing which domains and pages AI systems cite most&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;AI Search Trends for tracking which topics are gaining or losing momentum in AI prompts&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Shopping visibility to track product-level rankings in AI commerce recommendations&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Agent Experience Platform (AXP): actively delivers token-light, structured content to AI bots at the edge without altering the human-facing site; reduces token loads by up to 26% to unblock AI agents stuck on complex website markup (Enterprise-only)&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Persona-level filtering by country, language, and competitor set&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Ahrefs Brand Radar Tracks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Ahrefs Brand Radar is an add-on module within the broader Ahrefs platform. It tracks brand presence across AI answers and layers that data alongside traditional search demand, web mentions, video, and Reddit. Where Scrunch is purpose-built for AI visibility, Brand Radar is designed for teams that want AI monitoring without leaving the Ahrefs ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Key capabilities include:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;AI brand mentions across 7 AI platforms: AI Overviews, AI Mode, ChatGPT, Copilot, Gemini, Perplexity, and Grok&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;406M+ real search-backed monthly prompts derived from real user keywords (not synthetic) for benchmarking brand presence at scale&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Custom query filtering by prompt type, brand, and AI platform&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Bot Analytics for tracking AI bot behavior on your site&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;MCP Server: pull live Ahrefs data directly into Claude or ChatGPT&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Traditional search demand data from the Ahrefs keyword database (Site Explorer: 20.4B pages, Keywords Explorer, Rank Tracker, Site Audit with 170+ checks)&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Web mention monitoring across the open web&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;YouTube and video citation tracking; TikTok (beta); Reddit discussion monitoring&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Third-party citation source intelligence: understand why competitors are being cited (G2 reviews, Reddit threads, editorial coverage)&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scrunch vs Ahrefs Data Methodology Explained&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;AI visibility data is only as trustworthy as the methodology behind it. This is where I’d encourage any team to push harder before they buy.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How Scrunch Collects Data&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Scrunch uses a combination of browser automation and official platform APIs, then applies machine learning and NLP to surface brand mentions, sentiment, and citation patterns. Prompts run daily for the first 14 days after setup, then shift to a 72-hour refresh cadence by default. You can manually trigger a fresh response at any time.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;One nuance worth noting: Scrunch’s prompt architecture converts keyword data into prompts rather than sampling actual user queries from live AI traffic. For teams tracking a specific set of brand-relevant questions, this gives you precise control. For teams trying to model what real buyers are actually asking, it’s a gap worth acknowledging.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How Ahrefs Brand Radar Collects Data&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Ahrefs Brand Radar draws from a pool of &lt;a href="https://ahrefs.com/brand-radar"&gt;406M+ total monthly prompts&lt;/a&gt; derived from real user keywords (not synthetic) and lets you build custom queries to filter by prompt type, brand, and AI platform. The scale is an advantage: you’re benchmarking against a broader signal, not just the prompts your team wrote.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The documented limitations are worth flagging: third-party reviews report accuracy gaps in ChatGPT and Perplexity tracking specifically. Claude is not currently covered, which matters for teams whose ...

&lt;p&gt;AI SEO tools for small businesses are essential to keep up with marketing trends and stay competitive. Yet most small businesses are trying to figure out which AI tools are actually worth their time and which ones are necessary, especially when there is an abundance of tools promising to solve every problem imaginable. The good news is that AI is available in just about every tool.&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=9dd5e54b-fbef-4dd0-bc44-1689feb1ea18&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Get Started with HubSpot's AEO Tool" height="58" width="335" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/9dd5e54b-fbef-4dd0-bc44-1689feb1ea18.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The truth is that small businesses have to invest in AI SEO tools, either in time or with cash. The stats show it clearly: AI in marketing is growing. According to HubSpot’s latest &lt;a href="https://offers.hubspot.com/ai-marketing"&gt;AI Trends for Marketers&lt;/a&gt; report, two-thirds of marketers globally use AI in their role. Among American marketers, that number climbs to 74%.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;This guide cuts through the noise. It covers the essential AI SEO tools for small businesses that lean teams are actually using to do more with less. It includes free essentials like Google Search Console (GSC) and Google Analytics (GA4), and dedicated, paid-for platforms like HubSpot.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#which-ai-seo-tools-for-small-businesses-deliver-ongoing-value"&gt;Which AI SEO tools for small businesses deliver ongoing value?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#what-ai-can-and-cant-do-for-small-business-seo"&gt;What AI Can and Can’t Do for Small-Business SEO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#ai-seo-tools-for-small-business"&gt;AI SEO Tools for Small Business&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#frequently-asked-questions-about-ai-seo-tools-for-small-business"&gt;Frequently Asked Questions About AI SEO Tools for Small Businesses&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="#the-right-ai-seo-tool-is-the-one-that-solves-many-problems"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2 style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;Which AI SEO tools for small businesses deliver ongoing value?&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;AI SEO tools help small businesses research keywords, create content, optimize pages, fix technical issues, and track visibility. Choosing the right SEO tools based on what they can do for business is what’s challenging. Generally, small business buyers should prioritize time-to-value, learning curve, cost, and integration ease.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://53.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hub/53/hubfs/image9-Jul-17-2026-10-20-05-2016-AM.png?width=650&amp;amp;height=374&amp;amp;name=image9-Jul-17-2026-10-20-05-2016-AM.png" width="650" height="374" alt="AI seo tools for small businesses key considerations" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; width: 650px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;Time-to-Value&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Time-to-value measures how quickly a tool delivers useful output after setup.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Time-to-value matters enormously for a lean team without a dedicated SEO resource. A tool that requires two weeks of configuration, or an external consultant to come in and set it up, may be more trouble than it’s worth. Unless, of course, the business is certain the investment is worth it.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Think about how quickly the business needs the tool to be live and running, and what the impact is on workflows and other business priorities. Sometimes, the time (and potentially cash) investment is worth it. Other times, a tool that runs with minimal setup and can surface recommendations within 24 hours is more appealing.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s a real-life scenario showing how to think about time-to-value:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;If I’m working with a new client, certain tools are a no-brainer. For example, Google Search Console (GSC) is a free tool, and the data it provides is invaluable. I tell all my clients to set this up, or I do it for them. Once someone has added the tracking script to the website, the tool runs on its own in the background. Within 24 hours, I get valuable data about the website and SEO performance. It’s clear to me that GSC is a must-have for &lt;em&gt;all &lt;/em&gt;websites.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Compared to GSC, HubSpot requires more time to set up. If unlocking certain features is required, a cash investment is required, too, because some of HubSpot’s features are only available in higher editions.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The difference here is that GSC does a few things really well, such as:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Shows exactly which search queries are driving impressions and clicks.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Identifies indexing issues and crawl errors that Google has flagged.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Tracks average position and click-through rate by page and keyword.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Flags Core Web Vitals issues affecting page experience.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Submits sitemaps and requests re-indexing after page updates.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;HubSpot does a lot of things really well and adds a layer of sophistication to marketing and other business operations. For example, HubSpot:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Features AI-powered SEO recommendations that prioritize what to fix and why.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Has content optimization tools that help teams draft, refine, and publish on-brand content.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Tracks organic performance alongside email, ads, and CRM data in one place.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Connects SEO activity directly to leads and revenue in the same platform.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Automates reporting so teams aren’t manually pulling data from multiple tools.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Has a free CRM built in — contact, deal, and pipeline management without an extra subscription.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Connects SEO and content efforts directly to leads, deals, and revenue in the same platform.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Tracks the full customer journey from first organic visit to closed deal.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Features email marketing, landing pages, and forms that all live in the same ecosystem as SEO tools.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Includes social media management and ad tracking alongside organic performance data.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Automates lead nurturing workflows triggered by content engagement.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Features shared dashboards that mean sales and marketing teams work from the same data.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Scales with the business with free tools to start, and Pro and Enterprise editions as needs grow.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Reduces tool sprawl by replacing multiple point solutions with one platform.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Some tools may take more time to set up and require a payment. But these tools and their features may be business critical.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;If a tool can help save human hours and labor, influence marketing conversions, solve problems across the business, and directly contribute to business growth, then the time — and cash — investment is worth it. If a tool takes two weeks to set up and the marketing team never opens it, the value isn’t there.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;Learning Curve&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;A tool is only as useful as the team’s ability to use it consistently. Complex platforms built for enterprise SEO agencies often overwhelm ...

&lt;p&gt;Roughly &lt;a href="https://www.tryprofound.com/blog/ai-shopping-journey-2025"&gt;58% of consumers&lt;/a&gt; now use AI answer engines in their product research each week — and that number is rising fast. As AI-powered answer engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews become primary discovery surfaces, content and SEO teams are asking the right question:&lt;em&gt; is there a relationship between &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;backlinks and AEO&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;, or is it time to rethink the entire authority playbook?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=07ca2318-c9e0-4b5d-bcba-95cec5cb4958&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Download Now: The State of AEO in 2026 [Free AI Search Trends Report]" height="79" width="369" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/07ca2318-c9e0-4b5d-bcba-95cec5cb4958.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;The short answer is that contextually relevant backlinks carry more value than high-volume, low-relevance links for AEO. But they no longer tell the whole story.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;This post breaks down exactly how backlinks and AEO interact, where the differences between AEO and SEO show up in practice, and what a balanced authority strategy looks like right now.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Before diving in, keep in mind that tools like &lt;a href="https://www.hubspot.com/products/aeo"&gt;HubSpot AEO&lt;/a&gt; are built specifically to help marketing teams track and improve their brand’s visibility across AEO — more on that as we go.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Table of Contents&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#backlinks-and-aeo-what-changed-and-why-it-matters"&gt;Backlinks and AEO: What Changed and Why It Matters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#backlinks-and-aeo-do-links-still-move-the-needle"&gt;Backlinks and AEO: Do links still move the needle?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#differences-between-aeo-and-seo-in-practice"&gt;Differences Between AEO and SEO in Practice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#how-links-and-mentions-are-interpreted-by-answer-engines"&gt;How Links and Mentions Are Interpreted by Answer Engines&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#which-signals-beyond-links-matter-most"&gt;Which signals beyond links matter most?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#how-to-structure-content-for-backlinks-and-aeo-citations"&gt;How to Structure Content for Backlinks and AEO Citations&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#how-to-build-backlinks-and-aeo-salient-mentions-across-platforms"&gt;How to Build Backlinks and AEO-Salient Mentions Across Platforms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#measure-backlinks-and-aeo-impact-with-a-repeatable-loop"&gt;Measure Backlinks and AEO Impact with a Repeatable Loop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#frequently-asked-questions-about-backlinks-and-aeo"&gt;Frequently Asked Questions About Backlinks and AEO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="#backlinks-still-have-their-place"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2 style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;Backlinks and AEO: What Changed and Why It Matters&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Traditional search engines use backlinks as a primary authority signal. A link from a trusted domain to your page is, at its core, a vote of confidence — one that gets weighted by the linking domain’s own authority, the relevance of the context, and the anchor text used. Answer engines don’t abandon the traditional logic of &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/off-page-seo"&gt;off-page SEO&lt;/a&gt;. But they layer a great deal more on top of it.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;When an AI answer engine like ChatGPT or Google’s AI Overviews assembles a response, it isn’t simply ranking pages by backlink count. It is identifying sources that can reliably ground the answer. Those sources are:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Current content&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Content that is clearly structured&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;Content consistently associated with the right entities and topics&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;What this means for content and SEO teams is that a high-authority backlink profile is a necessary but no longer sufficient condition for AI visibility. That’s exactly the gap HubSpot AEO was built to close. The tool gives marketing teams a single place to monitor how often their brand appears in AI answers — and what content is driving (or missing from) that visibility.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2 style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;Backlinks and AEO: Do links still move the needle?&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Backlinks still matter for AEO, especially considering SEO is the foundation for any good AI search strategy. However, the type of link matters far more than it once did.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nathaniel-james-miller/"&gt;Nathaniel Miller&lt;/a&gt;, Head of Marketing at Ashbrook Technologies, said in a &lt;a href="https://cassieclarkmarketing.com/ai-search-and-backlinks/"&gt;recorded interview&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;em&gt;Found&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; in AI&lt;/em&gt; podcast: “The companies ranking highest across AI platforms tend to be the ones with both strong authority and strong backlink profiles.” He added that “if you’re not getting qualified traffic from that link, it’s basically a logo slap. The real value is in relevance and authority — not just size.”&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;In traditional SEO, strong domain authority and link volume influence rankings. But in AEO, relevance and semantic alignment between the linking source and your brand’s topic cluster matter much more. Here’s how different link types map to their influence in AEO versus classic SEO:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;div&gt; 
 &lt;table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; border: 3px none currentcolor;"&gt;
  &lt;colgroup&gt;
   &lt;col style="width: 30%;"&gt;
   &lt;col style="width: 23%;"&gt;
   &lt;col style="width: 47%;"&gt;
  &lt;/colgroup&gt; 
  &lt;tbody&gt; 
   &lt;tr style="height: 52px;"&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 30%; border: 1px solid #000000;"&gt; &lt;p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Link Type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 23%; border: 1px solid #000000;"&gt; &lt;p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Classic SEO Influence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 47%; border: 1px solid #000000;"&gt; &lt;p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;AEO Influence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; 
   &lt;/tr&gt; 
   &lt;tr style="height: 52px;"&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 30%; border: 1px solid #000000;"&gt; &lt;p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;High-DA, low-relevance link&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 23%; border: 1px solid #000000;"&gt; &lt;p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;High (domain authority boost)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 47%; border: 1px solid #000000;"&gt; &lt;p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Low (weak semantic signal)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/td&gt; 
   &lt;/tr&gt; 
   &lt;tr style="height: 52px;"&gt; 
    &lt;td style="vertical-align: top; width: 3...

&lt;p&gt;B2B SaaS businesses achieve an average &lt;a href="https://seoprofy.com/blog/seo-roi-statistics/"&gt;ROI of 702% from SEO&lt;/a&gt;, yet most teams are still using a SaaS SEO tool stack built for a different era of search.&lt;/p&gt;  
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="cta_button" href="https://www.hubspot.com/cs/ci/?pg=07e52e2e-2c66-4776-81a2-d2fc00199367&amp;amp;pid=53&amp;amp;ecid=&amp;amp;hseid=&amp;amp;hsic="&gt;&lt;img class="hs-cta-img " style="height: auto !important; width: auto !important; max-width: 100% !important;border-width: 0px; /*hs-extra-styles*/; margin: 0 auto; display: block; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px" alt="Download Now: HubSpot's Free AEO Guide" height="58" width="390" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/53/07e52e2e-2c66-4776-81a2-d2fc00199367.png" align="middle"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;For marketing teams that haven’t revisited their SaaS SEO tech stack recently, now is the time. The tools that powered growth two or three years ago may no longer cut it in an environment where visibility in AI-generated answers matters just as much as a first-page ranking.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;This guide covers 13 SaaS SEO tools. We selected each tool for a specific SaaS SEO workflow, covering research and technical audits, content optimization, AI search visibility, internal linking, and reporting.&lt;/p&gt; 
