&lt;h2&gt;What is AEO and why does it matter now?&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Think of AEO (or &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/generative-engine-optimization"&gt;GEO&lt;/a&gt;) as the AI-era companion to SEO. You’re not just chasing a ranking on a results page; you’re shaping what the AI says about your brand when a buyer asks a direct question.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Looking at &lt;a href="https://www.hubspot.com/company-news/aeo-data-buyers-using-ai-search-more-likely-to-purchase"&gt;HubSpot’s own data&lt;/a&gt;, 42% of CRM buyers are using AI search as part of their evaluation process. Furthermore, &lt;a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/what-web-strategists-think-about-sge"&gt;organic traffic for customers is down 27%&lt;/a&gt; year-over-year, while AI referral traffic has tripled. And here’s the kicker: AI-referred leads convert at 3x the rate of traditional search visitors.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;So, the urgency is warranted.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;AEO and SEO aren’t competing priorities. They work together. SEO drives qualified traffic through traditional search. AEO earns visibility in AI-generated answers. The best teams are investing in both.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;h3&gt;AEO vs SEO and How They Work Together&lt;/h3&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;AEO and SEO work together rather than replacing one another. They solve entirely different problems:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;ul&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;SEO improves discoverability in traditional search results, measuring success through rankings, click-through rates, and organic website visits.&lt;/li&gt; 
 &lt;li&gt;AEO improves brand visibility in AI-generated answers, measuring success by brand mentions, citations, share of voice, and sentiment.&lt;/li&gt; 
&lt;/ul&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;A buyer asking “what’s the best CRM?” on ChatGPT may never click to your site, but if ChatGPT names your brand positively, they are primed to convert. In fact, &lt;a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/ai-search-traffic-conversions-ahrefs/"&gt;Ahrefs data shows&lt;/a&gt; that AI search visitors have generated a 23x better conversion rate than traditional organic search.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Now here’s the question marketing teams are wrestling with: do you need a purpose-built AI visibility tool like HubSpot AEO to optimize for AI-generated answers, or does a full-suite SEO platform like &lt;a href="https://seranking.com/"&gt;SE Ranking&lt;/a&gt; (which has added AI tracking features) cover enough ground?&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;h2&gt;HubSpot AEO vs SE Ranking Overview&lt;/h2&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;Before diving into specific features and pricing, here’s our thought process in a nutshell:&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HubSpot &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AEO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is the specialist.&lt;/strong&gt; It is built specifically for AI visibility and tracks how your brand appears in answers from ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SE Ranking is the generalist.&lt;/strong&gt; It is a comprehensive SEO suite covering rank tracking, site audits, and backlink analysis, and it recently added a growing AI search toolkit to its platform. On its own, frankly, it leaves a lot to be desired for AEO. However, the team recently released a standalone AI visibility tool called &lt;a href="https://visible.seranking.com/"&gt;SE Visible&lt;/a&gt; that is more directly comparable to HubSpot AEO.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SE Visible&lt;/strong&gt; is a completely separate product from SE Ranking with its own login, pricing, and feature set, purpose-built to monitor how brands are represented, cited, and perceived across AI search platforms.&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;HubSpot AEO and SE Visible are the most apples-to-apples comparison for dedicated AI visibility tracking. At the same time, SE Ranking is best evaluated on its own merits as a traditional SEO suite with added AI monitoring capabilities.&lt;/p&gt; 
